Privacy Policy for TapConverter

Effective date: March 10, 2026

TapConverter (“we,” “our,” or “us”) provides a unit conversion mobile application for iOS. This Privacy Policy explains what information is collected, how it is used, and your choices.

1. Information We Collect

a) Information stored on your device
• TapConverter may store your recent conversion history locally on your device to improve app usability.
• This local data is not uploaded by us to our servers.

b) Advertising data (Google AdMob)
TapConverter uses Google AdMob to display ads. AdMob and its partners may collect certain information automatically, such as:
• Device identifiers
• IP address
• Approximate location
• Ad interaction and performance data
• Diagnostic and fraud-prevention signals

For details, see:
• Google Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy
• How Google uses information from sites/apps: https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites

2. How We Use Information

We use information to:
• Provide and operate TapConverter features
• Remember your app preferences/history locally
• Display and measure ads
• Maintain app security and prevent abuse/fraud

3. Data Sharing

We do not sell your personal information.

We may allow third-party service providers (such as Google AdMob) to process data as needed to provide advertising, analytics, and fraud prevention services.

4. Tracking and Personalized Ads

Depending on your region and device settings, ads may be personalized or non-personalized.

You can manage ad/tracking settings on iOS:
• Settings > Privacy & Security > Tracking
• Settings > Privacy & Security > Apple Advertising

5. Children’s Privacy

TapConverter is not directed to children under 13 (or the equivalent minimum age in your jurisdiction).
We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

6. Data Retention

• Local conversion history remains on your device until you clear it or uninstall the app.
• Third-party providers (e.g., AdMob) retain data according to their own policies.

7. Your Rights

Depending on your location, you may have rights regarding personal data (such as access, deletion, or objection).
For AdMob-related data requests, please refer to Google’s privacy controls and policies.

8. Security

We use reasonable measures to protect information processed through the app.
However, no method of transmission or storage is completely secure.

9. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.
We will post the updated version with a new effective date.

